The high 50s through lvl65 can be a tough time for equipment.  The items you've been wearing that were just fine up to the low 50s just don't get the job done anymore.

Though I used a Windblade up until a few days ago when I was able to get a nice no drop pally only weapon, I like the suggestion of selling for a WMBS or heavy windriders.  Either of those weapons is a very respectable weapon, and I see many level 60+ pallys using them.  This is only if your strapped for cash, mind you, if you have some pp to upgrade, I'd keep the windblade.

Another suggestion, I would start doing LDoNs asap.  Specifically, North Ro (or Tak themed) LDoNs.  I know it seems like a long way off, but the plate armor for 1492pts out of Tak is very respectable, and, if augmented correctly, better than ornate in terms of stats (obviously you have to consider the right click effect of ornate when comparing the two, but to me, its not worth the kind of pp being asked...currently 250K and up on my server).  The XP in a high 50s level LDoN isn't what you'll get in plane of storms or plane of valor, but its not too terrible, and you'll start earning the pts you can utilize for new armor.  In addition, you get the opportunity at aug drops and drops off named.  If you have some higher lvl friends who will allow you to go along on lvl63+ dungeons, the xp actually gets very decent.

By the way, the player makes the character, not the equipment.  Equipment can make a good player better, but it cannot make a bad player good.  There are an amazing number of lvl60+ players out there who do not have a clue as to how to play their classes...equipment upgrades won't do them any good.  I know several players in RL who are great players, but don't play enough to accumulate the pp for better gear.  They rarely spend much time looking for groups as those who know them always jump at the opportunity to group with them.

